    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4597940">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4597940">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4597940)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4597940">
																		reasons
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mjl1" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4114197); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4114197&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252381" alt="MJL1" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4114197)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mjl1" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4114197); return false;" >MJL1</a></span> <span class="odate time_1587002382 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Apr 2020 01:59</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4597940">
									

<p>The inclusion of <a href="http://kaktuskontainer.wdfiles.com/local--files/rogetcox/Rosencomputers.png">this background</a> makes the whole thing hard to read.</p>
<p>While the art is something way better than anything I could make myself, it doesn't seem very professional for something called &quot;official portrait&quot; at least.</p>
<p>Rosen has interacted with Pattern Screamers <em>three times</em> (<a href="/scp-000">SCP-000</a>, <a href="/scp-s">SCP-S</a>, and <a href="/scp-2">SCP-2</a>), so why suddenly they're on a first name basis is beyond me. I know some people have a headcanon that the guy is involved with them in some way, but this is a step too far for my tastes. This is <em>doubly so</em> for a hub page which some people might take as more canon.</p>
<p>As a whole, this cheapens the pattern screamers for me. If this existed when I was first starting to get into them, then I would be 10 times less likely to be interested in that particular topic.</p>
<p>Edit: If this &quot;hub page&quot; was converted to a tale, I would retract my -1 vote. The revision history starts with the edit summary: &quot;Is it a tale? Is it a hub? You decide!&quot; Since we have character tags for a reason, and character hubs aren't a thing, then this should be a tale.</p>

							</div>

								
