					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/natvoltaic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2800867&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252381" alt="NatVoltaic" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2800867)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/natvoltaic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;" >NatVoltaic</a></span> <span class="odate time_1587448644 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Apr 2020 05:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4606621">
									

<p>Seconding the criticism that the background makes the text difficult to read &#8212; my eyes glaze over the lines and jump several paragraphs down to where it stops, and trying to keep focus on it is strenuous.</p>
<p>As for the rest: the humor is too up-front to land for me, with breaks in clinicality (&quot;Every inch of floor space&quot;) not helping matters, and the pattern screamer dialogue is so similar to other pattern screamer dialogue that it's borderline cliche (which, in turn, undermines how intriguing the Gephart scenario is). Rosen's characterization isn't interesting, either; the details we get are presented in too dull and matter-of-fact of a manner to elicit any reaction beyond &quot;oh, so this is what they're like.&quot; At no point did they feel compelling.</p>
<p>As a navigational hub this is serviceable, but as a way to introduce new readers to the character this falls flat. -1</p>

							</div>

								
					
